'''Bicyclic phosphate''' is a class of bicyclic [[organophosphate]] compound that are used as [[flame retardant]]s, stabilizers and [[antioxidant]]s. They are also used in spectroscopic studies.<ref name="bp">{{cite journal |last1=Bellet |first1=E. M. |last2=Casida |first2=J. E. |title=Bicyclic Phosphorus Esters: High Toxicity without Cholinesterase Inhibition |journal=Science |date=14 December 1973 |volume=182 |issue=4117 |pages=1135–1136 |doi=10.1126/science.182.4117.1135|bibcode=1973Sci...182.1135B }}</ref><ref name="cwa">{{cite book |editor1-last=Gupta |editor1-first=Ramesh C. |title=Handbook of toxicology of chemical warfare agents |date=2009 |publisher=Academic Press |location=London |isbn=9780123744845 |edition=1st }}</ref>
Some bicyclic phosphates, such as [[TBPS]], [[TBPO]] and [[IPTBO]], are highly toxic. They have toxicity comparable to [[nerve agent]]s. However, they are not acetylcholinesterase inhibitors.<ref name="bp"></ref> They act as GABA receptor antagonists and have potent [[convulsant]] effects.<ref name="cwa"></ref><ref>{{cite journal |last1=BOWERY |first1=N. G. |last2=COLLINS |first2=J. F. |last3=HILL |first3=R. G. |title=Bicyclic phosphorus esters that are potent convulsants and GABA antagonists |journal=Nature |date=17 June 1976 |volume=261 |issue=5561 |pages=601–603 |doi=10.1038/261601a0|bibcode=1976Natur.261..601B }}</ref><ref name="cwa2">{{cite book |last1=Ellison |first1=D. Hank |title=Handbook of chemical and biological warfare agents |date=2007 |publisher=CRC |location=Boca Raton, Fla. |isbn=9780849314346 |edition=2nd }}</ref>
