The '''Pakistan Nursing Council (PNC)''' is a [[regulatory body]] established in 1948 by the Pakistan Nursing Council Act (1952, 1973).<ref>http://www.pnc.org.pk/admin/uploaded/PNC%20Act%201973.pdf</ref> PNC is empowered to license [[nurses]], [[midwives]], lady health visitors (LHVs) and nursing auxiliaries to practice throughout the country.<ref>http://www.pnc.org.pk</ref>
